he criminal" and "the political" with a "politics of living" that casts slum and state in opposition to one another. Living Politics shows us how legitimate domains of politics are redefined, how state sovereignty is forcibly enacted, and how the production of new citizen identities crystallize at the intersections of race, gender, and class.     aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aCommunity organizationzSouth Africa. 0aEnvironmental degradationxPolitical aspectszSouth Africa. 0aPolitical activistszSouth Africa. 0aSquatter settlementszSouth Africa. 0aSquattersxPolitical activityzSouth Africa. 0aUrban poorxPolitical activityzSouth Africa. 4aSouth Africa. 4acities. 4acitizenship. 4aenvironment. 4agender. 4agovernance. 4apolitics. 4apoverty. 4arace. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226519838423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226519838.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-063851-6  DG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019c2016d2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles